	     Pretoria – There were chaotic scenes at Grove Mall on Thursday morning when the owner of a jewellery store shot at a group of about five to seven suspects who robbed the store and got away with several valuable items. "There is information that suggests the owner [of the store] did manage to shoot at the intruders and currently we suspect that one of the suspects was injured," police spokesperson Captain Daniel Mavimbela said. READ: Shooting rocks Pretoria shopping mall Several glass display cases in the jewellery shop were broken and shattered glass was strewn across the store, which spilled out of the entrance. Mavimbela said an undisclosed amount of jewellery was taken. Police added that all of the suspects managed to get away. Terrified shoppers scattered around the mall when shots rang out. Two witnesses said they heard between four to five gunshots. The crime scene has been cordoned off and the police’s forensic unit combed the store for evidence. The rest of the mall is still open and its business as usual for shoppers. There has been a shooting at the grove mall in Pretoria following an unknown amount of suspects that tried to rob a jewellery store. One of the entrances of the mall has been closed @TeamNews24 pic.twitter.com/FJoPHKaXeI  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  